// useSyncScroll
// Synchronizes scroll position between an editor pane and a preview pane using proportional scroll ratios.

Proportional scroll: scrollTop / (scrollHeight - clientHeight) is computed on the source and applied to the target.
A scrollSource ref prevents feedback loops — while one pane is driving, the other's handler is suppressed.
Sync can be toggled at runtime; the enabled prop sets the initial state.

FUNCTION useSyncScroll({ editorRef, previewRef, enabled, debounceMs }) -> { isSynced, toggleSync, enableSync, disableSync }  EXPORT
  Manages state: isSynced (initially from enabled prop).
  When isSynced is true, attaches debounced scroll handlers to both the editor and preview elements.
  Removes handlers when isSynced becomes false or the component unmounts.

---

FUNCTION handleEditorScroll()
  Skipped if the preview is currently driving the scroll.
  Computes the proportional scroll position of the editor and applies it to the preview.
  Sets scrollSource to "editor" and clears it after debounceMs.

---

FUNCTION handlePreviewScroll()
  Skipped if the editor is currently driving the scroll.
  Computes the proportional scroll position of the preview and applies it to the editor.
  Sets scrollSource to "preview" and clears it after debounceMs.

---

FUNCTION toggleSync()
  Flips isSynced between true and false.

---

FUNCTION enableSync()
  Sets isSynced to true.

---

FUNCTION disableSync()
  Sets isSynced to false.

---

FUNCTION debounce(fn, delay) -> fn
  Returns a debounced version of fn that waits delay ms after the last call before executing.
